# Tailwind Primary Styling Engine

- ALWAYS default to Tailwind CSS utility classes for component styling.
- Use the global Tailwind configuration (`tailwind.config.js` or equivalent) as the source of truth for tokens (colors, spacing, typography, breakpoints).
- Do NOT write custom CSS/SCSS when the style can be achieved cleanly with standard or configured Tailwind utilities.
- In Tailwind, use theme-mapped classes (for example `text-primary`, `gap-4`) instead of arbitrary values unless explicitly justified by a tokenized pattern.
- NEVER hardcode structural magic numbers in class composition or inline styles when a tokenized utility exists.
